This module provides utilities for building a hierarchical tree structure from a flat list of documentation entries.

## Purpose

The `buildTree` function transforms an array of `ManifestEntry` objects, each containing a `docKey` and `title`, into a nested tree structure. This is useful for organizing and displaying documentation in a navigation or file-explorer-like interface.

## Key Exports

### `FileNode` Type

A type representing a file in the documentation tree.

```typescript
{
  kind: "file";
  name: string;
  key: string;
  title: string;
}
```

### `FolderNode` Type

A type representing a folder in the documentation tree.

```typescript
{
  kind: "folder";
  name: string;
  children: TreeNode[];
}
```

### `TreeNode` Type

A union type that can be either a `FileNode` or a `FolderNode`.

```typescript
FileNode | FolderNode;
```

### `buildTree(entries: ManifestEntry[]): TreeNode[]`

Constructs a hierarchical tree from a list of manifest entries. It iterates through each entry, splits its `docKey` into segments to create folders, and places the file node at the appropriate level in the tree. The resulting tree is sorted alphabetically by node name, with folders appearing before files at the same level.

**Parameters:**
*   `entries`: An array of `ManifestEntry` objects, where each entry has at least `docKey` (string) and `title` (string) properties.

**Returns:**
An array of `TreeNode` objects representing the root level of the documentation tree.

## Usage Example

```typescript
import type { ManifestEntry } from "../types";
import { buildTree, TreeNode } from "./tree";

const manifestEntries: ManifestEntry[] = [
  { docKey: "getting-started/introduction", title: "Introduction" },
  { docKey: "getting-started/installation", title: "Installation" },
  { docKey: "guides/authentication/basic", title: "Basic Authentication" },
  { docKey: "guides/authentication/oauth", title: "OAuth" },
  { docKey: "api/users", title: "Users API" },
];

const tree: TreeNode[] = buildTree(manifestEntries);

console.log(JSON.stringify(tree, null, 2));

/*
Output:
[
  {
    "kind": "folder",
    "name": "api",
    "children": [
      {
        "kind": "file",
        "name": "users",
        "key": "api/users",
        "title": "Users API"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "kind": "folder",
    "name": "guides",
    "children": [
      {
        "kind": "folder",
        "name": "authentication",
        "children": [
          {
            "kind": "file",
            "name": "basic",
            "key": "guides/authentication/basic",
            "title": "Basic Authentication"
          },
          {
            "kind": "file",
            "name": "oauth",
            "key": "guides/authentication/oauth",
            "title": "OAuth"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "kind": "folder",
    "name": "getting-started",
    "children": [
      {
        "kind": "file",
        "name": "installation",
        "key": "getting-started/installation",
        "title": "Installation"
      },
      {
        "kind": "file",
        "name": "introduction",
        "key": "getting-started/introduction",
        "title": "Introduction"
      }
    ]
  }
]
*/
```
